President Obama announced his intent to nominate Jane D. Hartley as the Ambassador to the French Republic, Department of State. Hartley is currently the CEO of Observatory Group, LLC and has held various positions in broadcasting and corporate communications. She has also served on the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service and is a member of several other boards and committees.

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Mia Guttfreund Lehrer as a member of the Commission of Fine Arts. Lehrer is the President of Mia Lehrer & Associates, a landscape architecture firm, and has previously served on various committees for the City of Los Angeles. She is also a member of several professional organizations in her field.

Both Hartley and Lehrer bring a wealth of experience and talent to their new roles and President Obama looks forward to working with them in the future.